cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CT, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as ornaments are a concept in dependently-typed theory, which is a subfield of logic in computer science. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as ornaments are a technique for managing the proliferation of special-purpose datatypes, which is a common problem in programming language design. 
- cs.CT (Category Theory) is relevant as the paper presents a categorical model of ornaments. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as ornaments are a technique for structuring data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as ornaments can be seen as a software engineering technique for managing complexity in dependently-typed programming.
